Coach Luciano Spalletti has admitted that Napoli failed to take advantage of Victor Osimhen’s one-on-one style in their 2-3 loss to Fiorentina.   The coach who is not giving up on their title chase said: “We had tried to take advantage of Osimhen’s one on one but we were not precise and we stretched a little. In the second half, we came back well, we were managing the game after the draw and then on a ball that we played many times in the first half. they built the goal. Then it was all more difficult, we had rough management on their third goal. At 1-1, we had the game in hand.”   Fans brace up for Heineken’s UCL Trophy Tour with…     Man City keep  title lead after thrilling draw with…     Napoli 2-3 Fiorentina: Osimhen closes in on Nwankwo’s Serie…   Meanwhile, Victor Osimhen’s 84th-minute goal could not save Napoli as the defeat dented their hopes of a first Serie A title in more than three decades. Osimhen was on throughout the encounter but  struggled all day to get the better of the brilliant Fiorentina defender Igor Julio. But Osimhen smashed home his 12th  goal of the season.